    "chemicalDescription": [
      "Acetyl Isoleucyl D-Oligopeptide-1 Amide is the product obtained by the acetylation of the synthetic peptide containing 15 amino acids consisting of D-arginine, L-isoleucine, D-leucine, D-lysine, D-phenylalanine, D-tryptophan and D-valine in which the C-terminus is an amide. The L conformation of the oligopeptide is based on a 12 amino acid sequence from Vipericidin which is found in the eastern brown snake."
    ],
